      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JAMARRA (1) was unwanted in betting when starting from the same box but ran very well, finishing in the minors over 730m at Angle Park in a Grade 3/4/5 in 43.60. Has good early burn and suited drawn the inside. Should be in this for a long way. NITROUS (7) steps out for the first time at this course. Missed the frame last time when 4th and beaten 12 lengths (43.80) at Angle Park. Better than last start and can bounce back. COMPTON ROCKY (5) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Murray Bridge behind Nova's Fern (30.29) in a Grade 6. The form from his last run stacks up well. Expecting another good run. CANYA VIVI (3) should be thereabouts after filling a top-three spot in a fast run most recently.",
